    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-15T21:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-15T21:32:00-05:00" n="773"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–1353: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d773fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-15T22:32:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1953—10:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 79. You authorized give <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> firmest assurances US Government made no
                    suggestions officially or unofficially encourage Kashmir government seek
                    satisfaction any given set demands. You may assure <persName>Nehru
                        Stevenson</persName> given no mission discuss Kashmir with <persName
                        corresp="#p_ASM1">Abdullah</persName> or anyone else.</p>
                <p>In light current misunderstandings among Indian officials public you may wish
                    instruct your staff refrain visits Kashmir for present.</p>
                <p>While making clear <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> complete lack
                    substance charges our interference Kashmir you should remind him our real hope
                    forthcoming negotiations will provide progress Kashmir solution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
